  <section class="ps-faq">
    <h2>Subscription <em>questions</em>.</h2>
    <details>
      <summary>Where do you deliver subscriptions?</summary>
      <p>Free hand-delivery to ZIPs 10032, 10033, 10034, 10040, 10031, and 10039. That covers all of Washington Heights, Hudson Heights, Inwood, and Hamilton Heights. Marble Hill (10463) and the Cloisters area are included. Outside that zone, we add a small fee at checkout.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Can I pause or skip a week?</summary>
      <p>Yes. Log into your account or text the shop at (917) 770-1684. We can pause, skip a single week, or change the delivery day. No fees, no contracts, no questions.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>What if I'm not home?</summary>
      <p>We leave bouquets in a vestibule or with a doorman if you have one. Most of the buildings on Fort Washington and Pinehurst know us by sight. If you'd rather pick up at the shop, we'll hold it cooled until 6 PM.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Can I gift a subscription?</summary>
      <p>Yes. Familia is the most-gifted tier. Choose "gift" at checkout, add the recipient's address, and pick how many weeks. We'll include a handwritten note in your name and email you when each delivery lands.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>What if I just want roses, not a subscription?</summary>
      <p>That's why we built the rose menu. A dozen pink garden roses, classic red, or white with eucalyptus. Hand-tied at the bench and walked to your door same day. <a href="/pages/roses">See the rose menu</a>.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>¿Hablan español?</summary>
      <p>Sí. Toda la familia. Si prefieres ordenar o coordinar entregas en español, llámanos al (917) 770-1684 o pásate por la tienda en 463 Fort Washington Ave. <a href="/pages/florista-washington-heights">Ver en español</a>.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>How do I cancel?</summary>
      <p>From your account in two clicks. Or text the shop. Or walk in. We don't make people stay who don't want to. Subscription floral is the long game and only works when you actually want the flowers.</p>
    </details>
  </section>

